EX NO: 5a
CONVERTING TEXT TO UPPER CASE 
AIM:
	To Write a JavaScript code that converts the entered text into uppercase.
PROCEDURE:

1.	Click the start button and select the program --accessories    --    notepad
2.	Include the script tag and add mention the language of java script.
3.	Declare a variable varchar str assign the text as “HELLO”.
4.	Declare another variable str1 and assign the operator to uppercase to start to convert lowercase letter to uppercase.
5.	Print the output using document write function.
6.	If any error occurs correct by right clicking select the editing source from menu.


 PROGRAM

<html>
<head>
<title>Lowercase to uppercase</title>
<head>
<body>
<script language="JavaScript">
var str=new String("Hello")
var str1=str.toUpperCase();
document.write("The upper case String for "+str+" is "+str1);
</script>
</body>
</html>

RESULT
	
Thus the program is executed and output is verified.

