EX NO: 6
FRAMES & EVENTS
AIM:

	Write a java script code using frames and event (when) cursor moves over an object it should display the specification of the object in another frame.

PROCEDURE:

1.	Click the start button and select the program --accessories    --    notepad
2.	Include the script tag and add the language as java script.
3.	Include frames by using frameset tag.
4.	Create first frame .Include FORM tag and mouse move event in it. And save the file.
5.	Create second frame and include textbox in it .Save it in another file.
6.	Execute the program in any one browser.
7.	Check when mouse cursor moves the output displayed in next frame.
8.	If any error occurs correct by right clicking select the editing source from menu..

PROGRAM

MAIN.HTML

<html>
<head>
<title>Frames Values</title>
</head>
<frameset cols="20%,80%">
<frame src="frame1.html"name="left_frame">
<frame src="frame2.html"name="right_frame">
</frameset>	<noframes>
</noframes>
</html>
Frame1.HTML
<html>
<head>
<title>frame1 event</title>
</head>
<body>
<form>
<p>
<input type="button" value="what is cool?"onMouseMove="parent.right_frame.document.form1.text1.value='What is cool?'">
</p>
<input type="button" value="what is hot?"onMouseMove="parent.right_frame.document.form1.text1.value='What is hot?'">
</p>
<p>&nbsp;
</p>
</form>
</body>
</html>

Frame2.HTML 
<html>
<head>
<title>frame 2</title>
<head>
<body>
<form name="form1">
<input type="text" name="text1" size="25" value=" ">
</form>
</body>
</html>












OUTPUT

 



RESULT

	Thus the program is executed and output is verified.



















EX NO: 7
SITE FOR BANNER ADVERTISEMENT
AIM:

	To create a site containing banner advertisement at the top of the page the ads are changed every 10 or 15 seconds.
PROCEDURE:

1.	Click the start button and select the program --accessories    --    notepad
2.	Within the notepad type the necessary script tag and html tags..
3.	Get the array of images.
4.	Using the function startTime() create the advertisement banner,.
5.	Save the file using .html extension.
6.	Execute the program in any browser and view the output.
7.	If any error occurs correct by right clicking select the editing source from menu.
PROGRAM
 <html>
<head>
<title> Advertisement Banner</title>
<script language=”javascript” type=”text/javascript”>
var timerid=0;
var images=new array (“image1.jpg”,
”image2.jpg”,
”image3.jpg”);
var  countimages=0;
function StartTime()
{
If(timerid)
{
Timerid=0;
}
Var tDate=new Date();
If(countimages= =images.length)
{
Countimages=0;
}
If(tDate.getSeconds()%5= =0)
{
document.getElementById(“img1”).src=images[countimages];
}
Countimages++;
Timerid=setTimeOut(“startTime()”,1000);
}
</script>
</head>
<body onload=”startTime();”>
<img id=”img1” src=”image1.jpg” height=”500” width=”600” align=”center”> SNGPC></img>
</body>
</html>
OUTPUT

 




RESULT
