EX NO: 8
JQUERY FOR COUNT THE SECONDS BETWEEN CLICK EVENTS
AIM:

	To create a Jquery program for count the number of milliseconds between two click events on a paragraph.
PROCEDURE:

1.	Click the start button and select the program --accessories    --    notepad
2.	Within the notepad include the jquery library.
3.	Add jquery script for count the milliseconds between two click events.
4.	Add necessary HTML tags.
5.	Execute the program using any browser.
6.	If any errors occur correct it by right click editing source from menu.

PROGRAM

<html>
<head>
<script src="file:///C:/Documents%20and%20Settings/CSE/My%20Documents/karthika/html/jquery-3.2.1.min.js"></script>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title> jsbin</title>
<script>
$(document).ready(function(){
var lastt, tdiff;
$( "p" ).click(function( event ) {
  if (lastt) {
    tdiff = event.timeStamp - lastt;
    $( "div" ).append( "Time since last event: " + tdiff + "<br>" );
  } else {
    $( "div" ).append( "<br>Click again.<br>" );
  }
  lastt = event.timeStamp;
  });
});
</script>
</head>
<body>
<p>Count the number of milliseconds between the two click events on a paragraph </p>
  <div>Click on the above paragraph</div>
</body>
</html>
OUTPUT

 



RESULT:
	Thus the program is executed and output is verified.





